task.summary: Default task
Add util methods for changing image's perspective and affining image. Add method for generating a group of rotated images and method for scaled images.
Add perspective-change methods to ImageProcessor and add a test for those methods in Main
Add test for matching precision of specifically-distorted images
Bug fix: didn't give result descriptor type in extractRoubstFeature(). Add test on regression matching distance threshold.
Bug fix: regression match includes original match result. Bug fix: use BruteForce match to extract distortion feature points
remove symmetry test in matchWithRegression.
Fix a bug in robust feature points extraction: now the program use template feature points as query to match FP in distorted images.
Bug fix: in sortedRobustFeatures(), after sorting the feature points the original feature list rather than sorted list was used to return.
matchWithRegression(): guarantee the matching is injective
Add debug message and create Vegeta images of different angles.
Match between original image and distorted images
In matchWithRegression(), set position distance threshold according to the original matches' position differences rather than a fixed number.
test if distortion makes sense in real images
print out matched key points in testRegularFP()
Sort files in testRegularFP()
Pick the match with minimum distance if multiple query points are matched to same template point in Main.testRegularFP().
Randomly pick specific number of regular feature points and then do matching in Main.testRegularTF().
Main.testRegularFP(): only randomly pick template key points, keep query FP unchanged.
